We recommended that the Local Chief Executive instruct the: 

(a) Municipal Accountant to (i) update and maintain complete subsidiary records per individual borrower/debtor to facilitate the generation of accounting schedule which reconciles with the General Ledger (GL) controlling account for Receivables of the KNS;


(ii) take up the accrual of receivables from market stallholders and the corresponding revenues by debiting Accounts Receivable and crediting Receipts from Market Operations for ₱154,270.00;

(iii) draw adjusting journal entry to correct the Other Deferred Credits account and Prior Period Adjustment for ₱14,951,178.00; and

(iv) adhere strictly to the above provisions of law and accounting/ reporting standards relating to the maintenance of special accounts for each economic enterprise in the General Fund for purposes of promoting the principles of transparency and full disclosure of government operations; and

(b)	Market Supervisor to update and prepare, at least on a quarterly basis, the delinquency reports for the Public Market and furnish a copy to the Accounting Unit for recording and monitoring.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive (a) instruct the Inventory Committee to (i) conduct a complete physical count of all the properties of the Municipal Government on an annual basis;




(ii) reconcile the results of inventory-taking with the accounting records; and

(iii) submit to the Auditor’s Office the Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment with accurate descriptions and details not later than January 31 of each year;

(b) advise the Municipal Accountant to (i) exert effort to locate or retrieve the pertinent documents to substantiate the unaccounted balances and take necessary action to establish the accuracy of PPE balances; or

