9.20	We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the Municipal Environment Management Officer (MENRO) to:
(a) 	revise and submit immediately the Municipality’s 10-year Solid Waste Management Plan and take necessary action for its immediate approval with the purpose of ensuring its sustainability, viability, effectiveness, and relevance in relation to local and international developments in the field of solid waste management;
(b) Proceed immediately with the implementation of Safe Closure and Rehabilitation Plan of the controlled dumpsite facility as ordered by the DENR EMB Region III;
(c) 	Implement stricter control measures on the surroundings of the transfer station in accordance with DENR A.O. No. 2001 -34 dated December 20, 2001, so as to promote a zero waste, smoke-free and healthy environment; and
(d) Ensure that the existing MRFs of 14 component barangays are fully functional and provide the necessary technical or financial support to the remaining two barangays for the establishment of their own MRFs.

Stop the practice of spending for representation purposes beyond the budgetary ceiling;

Ensure the necessity of providing meals and snacks by considering the objectives and mandate of the office/organization;


Direct the Municipal Accountant to submit all the monthly accounts and financial reports to facilitate the audit of the major expenses of the LGU;

Abide strictly to the provisions of R.A. No. 9184 in the acquisition of goods and services, particularly meals and catering services to achieve the most advantageous contracts; and

Stop the practice of splitting purchase requests and observe strictly the conditions required before resorting to alternative mode of procurement; otherwise, transactions that are not in accordance with the Procurement Law shall be disallowed for being irregular/illegal in nature.

require the Municipal Accountant to: (i) submit immediately the disbursement vouchers and supporting documents of the projects undertaken for proper verification by the Audit Team; and (ii) prepare liquidation reports for fully implemented projects and return the balance to Source Agencies; 

instruct the OIC-Municipal Treasurer to sign box D of the DV and all supporting documents bearing his name; and


sign/approve the Disbursement vouchers and all supporting documents before payments be effected and the DVs/supporting documents already submitted to the Audit Team, otherwise, Notice of Suspensions (NS) will be issued by the Audit Team for the DVs without the signature/approval of the LCE.

plan and prioritize projects that provide long-term development, socio-economic development, and environmental management benefits to constituents in accordance with DBM-DILG Joint Memorandum Circular No. 2017-1 dated February 22, 2017; 

support the appropriation for 20% development projects with a listing of specific programs, projects, and activities to be undertaken to facilitate proper evaluation of its utilization pursuant to existing government laws, rules and regulations; 

coordinate with the Municipal Engineer in the inspection of projects upon completion to guarantee that the same were undertaken in accordance with the terms and conditions of the contract and used by the end-user for their intended purposes; 

instruct the Punong Barangay of Barangay Matain to undertake the evacuation of the informal settlers and facilitate the cleanliness and operation of the Barangay Health Center; 

unburden the 20% Development Fund with other charges, i.e. debt-servicing. Appropriate a reasonable amount for loan amortization based on the total regular income of the LGU after deduction of all its statutory and contractual obligations as provided under Section 324 (b) of the Local Government Code; 

coordinate with the Municipal Planning Development Officer in the preparation of the Report on Utilization or accomplishment reports on the use of 20% Development Fund, a copy of which to be submitted to the Audit Team; and 

