We recommended that management (a) instruct the Municipal Accountant to require the concerned accountable officer to liquidate/submit liquidation reports as soon as the purpose of the cash advance has been accomplished; 

(b) cause the refund/return of the excess cash advances, if any, for the full settlement thereof; 

(c) review the current practice on the submission of the reports to the Audit Team and take note of the timelines; 

(d) as much as possible, refrain from granting cash advances to non-organic personnel of the Municipality; and 

(e) strictly adhere to the limitations set forth by law specifically the grant of new cash advance to an accountable officer even though the previous cash accountabilities have not yet been settled.

