(ii) incur expenditures within the allotted budget; and 

(iii) submit utilization report within the deadline set; 


Municipal Budget Officer to carefully monitor the appropriation made available to SEF and the obligations chargeable thereto to avoid inappropriate utilization of unrealized income; and 

Municipal Accountant to submit the liquidation reports, together with the supporting documents to the Audit Team within the set due date for timely verification.

We recommended that management direct the Municipal Accountant to (a) submit to the Audit Team the CIF disbursement vouchers (DVs), together with the required supporting documents for the grant of cash advance, within the prescribed period of seven days from the release of the check in a sealed envelope for verification purposes; 

(b) process additional cash advances only after the liquidation of the previous ones; 


(c) provide certification on the DVs that the previous cash advance for the same purpose was already liquidated and proper accounting thereof has been made; and 

(d) henceforth, strictly adhere to the guidelines under COA-DBM-DILG-GCG-DND Joint Circular No. 2015-01 on the granting, recording, and reporting of confidential and/or intelligence funds for CY 2017 and the years thereafter.

